  "text": "Assays were run in 384-well plates with recombinant HDACs 1-9 (BPS Bioscience) under conditions appropriate for Michaelis-Menten kinetic analysis with the use of acetylated tripeptide substrates at K m that are amide-coupled to 7-amino-4-methylcoumarin that can detect either class I/IIb (substrate MAZ1600) or class IIa/HDAC8 (substrate MAZ1675) HDAC activity exactly as described in [CITATION_1] .",
